      "span_text": "User-level sandboxes have been used to intercept system call requests and may record, deny, reorder, replace, or dispatch any request. This approach offers significant flexibility because all system calls can be subjected to arbitrary handling by the sandbox. However, sandboxes that do this entirely within user space have difficulty supporting standard features like safe and efficient multi-threading [CITATION_1] ."
